SIMPLE: tweak
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tweak
<hw>Tweak</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>twikken</ets>, originally the same word as <ets>twicchen</ets>; cf.
LG. <ets>twikken</ets>. See <er>Twitch</er>.]</ety> <def>To pinch and
pull with a sudden jerk and twist; to twitch; <as>as, to <ex>tweak</ex>
the nose</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tweak</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tweak
<hw>Tweak</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sharp pinch or jerk; a
twist or twitch; <as>as, a <ex>tweak</ex> of the nose</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Trouble; distress; tweag.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A prostitute.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Brathwait.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tweed</ent>⟦br⟧
